<text>Accessing a radial bond&apos;s properties

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;

To access a radial bond&apos;s properties, double-click it when the model container is in the selection mode (i.e. the button &quot; &quot; is chosen), and you will see the following dialog window:

  
[This is a screenshot.]

This dialog box allows you to change the bond length and strength, choose the style and set the color for the selected bond (the default color is white).

Script support

To change a radial bond&apos;s properties, select it first and then call set strength [value] to change its strength and set bondlength [value] to change its bond length.

